<sect1 id="dir_bf15dcce3b0eb2b2bde353446d930b9c_1autotoc_md419">
<title>Architecture</title><para>The UI module follows the ECS pattern used throughout helios:</para>
<para>1. <bold>Components</bold> store UI-specific state (anchors, offsets, text content) 2. <bold>Systems</bold> process components each frame to update positions and content 3. <bold>Bindings</bold> connect game state (e.g., scores) to UI widgets</para>
<para>UI elements are positioned relative to viewports using anchors and offsets, allowing for resolution-independent layouts.</para>
